Anime Catalog Web Application

This is a full stack web application that allows users to browse a catalog of anime titles, view details about each anime, watch movie trailers related to the anime, and save selected anime to a SQL database.

Features
Browse Anime Catalog: 
Users can browse through a catalog of anime titles fetched from an Anime API.
<client/images/categories.png>

View Anime Details: 
Users can click on an anime title to view more details about the selected anime, including its synopsis, release date, genre, and rating.
<client/images/info.png>

Search Anime: 
Users can search anime by title to view their favorite anime.
<client/images/search.png>
<client/images/search_result.png>

Watch Movie Trailers: 
Users can watch movie trailers related to the selected anime directly within the application.
<client/images/trailer.png>
<client/images/play_trailer.png

Save Favorite Anime: 
Users can save their favorite anime titles to a SQL database by clicking on the "Save" button.
<client/images/save.png>
<client/images/SQL_DB.png>

Technologies Used
Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript
Backend: Node.js, Express.js
Database: SQL (PGAdmin, PostgreSQL)
External API: Anime API (API link, API Key and Authorization not required.)
Additional Libraries: Axios (for making HTTP requests)

Installation
Clone the repository:
bash

git clone https://github.com/mgdeveloper45/anime.git
Navigate to the project directory:
bash

cd server
Install dependencies:

npm install
Set up the database:

Create a SQL database to store the favorite anime titles.
Update the database configuration in the pgadmin file.
Set up API access:

Obtain API end routes from the Anime API provider.
Update the API configuration in the client/main.js file.
Start the server:

sql

nodemon server/server.js
Open your web browser and navigate to http://localhost:4001 to access the application.
Usage
Browse Anime Catalog: 
Explore the list of anime titles displayed on the homepage.

View Anime Details: 
Click on an anime title to view more details about the selected anime.

Watch Movie Trailers: 
Click on the "Play" button to watch movie trailers related to the selected anime.

Save Favorite Anime: 
Click on the "Save" button to save the selected anime to your favorites list.

Credits
Anime API: 
"https://kitsu.io/api/edge/anime?filter[text]=pokemon&page[limit]=1"
